## Step 4 — Remove the `DATE_FORMATTER` usage for today/yesterday from `DemandHandlerImpl`

`DemandHandlerImpl` no longer computes today/yesterday itself. Keep `DATE_FORMATTER` only if `toHistoricalFileName` or `getOnDemandFileName` still use it. Looking at `toHistoricalFileName`:

```java
private String toHistoricalFileName(String onDemandFileName, String today) {
    int dotIdx = onDemandFileName.lastIndexOf('.');
    String base = (dotIdx > 0) ? onDemandFileName.substring(0, dotIdx) : onDemandFileName;
    String ext = (dotIdx > 0) ? onDemandFileName.substring(dotIdx) : ".req";

    // 'today' now passed in — no LocalDate.now() here
    String historicalBase;
    if (base.endsWith("_U") || base.endsWith("_I")) {
        historicalBase = base.substring(0, base.length() - 2) + "_H_" + today;
    } else if (base.endsWith("_H")) {
        historicalBase = base + "_" + today;
    } else {
        historicalBase = base + "_H_" + today;
    }
    return historicalBase + ext;
}
```

It takes `today` as a parameter now — no internal `LocalDate.now()`. So `DATE_FORMATTER` may only be needed if nothing else uses it. If unused, remove the constant from `DemandHandlerImpl`.

