## One alternative if you prefer not to touch the DTO

If adding fields to `OnDemandScopeDetailsDto` feels heavy, you could compute the dates in `ProcessOnDemandRequestItemReader.initialize()` (also runs once) and pass them through. But the DTO approach is cleanest because the dates are per-item-accessible exactly where they're needed, and `initialize()` already calls `getVacationDetails` which is the single computation point.

